Data Transformation (Pushing some variables to factor) Note that the Month is pushed to a factor that have a new level for each month. However, in our dataset we have no observations for February and march. When I introduce this level in the table it shows no data for those two months. There are no NAs in our data, the level function just shows that there is no data for that month.

Data Description

There are 702 unique hurricanes in this dataset all the occurred in the north american region between the years 1950 to 2013. Data on the storms location (longitude & latitude) and maximum wind speed were recorded every 6 hours stored in the time variable. Data is also collected on the season (aka the year), the storms month, and the nature of the hurricane; (Extra Tropical (ET), Disturbance (DS), Not Rated (NR), Sub Tropical (SS), and Tropical Storm (TS)). The number of observations we have for each storm range from 1 to 118 with a mean value of 31 observations.

library(lubridate)

dt_temp = dt %>%
  mutate(
    Nature = factor(Nature),
    Season = factor(Season), # season is year not season.... 
    Month = factor(Month, levels = c(month.name)),
  ) %>%  
  tidyr::separate(
    time, c('Date', 'Time'), 
                       sep = ' ', extra = 'merge') %>% 
  tidyr::separate(
    Date, c('year_num', 'month_num', 'day'), 
                       sep = '-', extra = 'merge') %>% 
  tidyr::separate(
    Time, c('hour', 'min', 'sec'), 
                       sep =':', extra = 'merge')  %>%
  select(-c(year_num, month_num, sec)) %>%
  select(ID, Nature, Latitude, Longitude, Wind.kt, Season, Month, day, hour, min)
